      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\CHANGELOG.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Changelog\n2: \n3: All notable changes to AgentSON will be documented here. AgentSON uses [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n4: \n5: ## [0.1.0] - 2026-07-05\n6: \n7: Initial public release. Apache 2.0 license.\n8: \n9: ### Specification\n10: \n11: - **JSON Schema v1** (`spec/v1.json`) — 8 entry types: `user-query`, `context`, `querying`, `title`, `thought`, `action`, `answer`, `side-effect`\n12: - **JSON Schema v1.1** (`spec/v1.1.json`) — Trajectory semantics: `task`, `outcome`, `observation` entry type, `tool_call_id`, `correlation_id`, `status` on all entries, `duration_ms`, `error` on actions\n13: - Backward compatible: all v1.0 files validate against v1.1\n14: \n15: ### Readers (6)\n16: \n17: - `readers/opencode.py` — opencode SQLite sessions\n18: - `readers/minimax.py` — MiniMax SQLite sessions\n19: - `readers/antigravity.py` — Antigravity IDE protobuf sessions\n20: - `readers/libre.py` — FreeStyle Libre 2 CSV glucose data\n21: - `readers/chrome_devtools.py` — Chrome DevTools AI session traces (9 tests)\n22: - `readers/claude_code.py` — Claude Code JSONL session transcripts\n23: \n24: ### Importers (1)\n25: \n26: - `importers/chatgpt.py` — ChatGPT `conversations.json` → AgentSON\n27: \n28: ### Exporters (1)\n29: \n30: - `exporters/finetune.py` — Unsloth (ShareGPT) + Olive (chat-messages) training formats\n31: \n32: ### CLI\n33: \n34: - `agentson export` — Export sessions from any supported tool\n35: - `agentson import` — Import ChatGPT conversations\n36: - `agentson list` — List sessions with metadata\n37: - `agentson search` — Full-text search across sessions\n38: - `agentson finetune` — Export to training formats\n39: - `agentson render` — Render sessions as Markdown\n40: - `agentson push` — Push to Supabase (optional)\n41: - `agentson pull` — Pull from Supabase (optional)\n42: \n43: ### Web Viewer\n44: \n45: - `docs/viewer/index.html` — Full-featured: file extension + schema validation, download as .AgentSON, search/filter, sort toggle, copy per entry, side-by-side layout, role-based colors, collapsible JSON metadata preview\n46: - `pwa/` — Standalone PWA with offline support\n47: \n48: ### Documentation\n49: \n50: - 14 SOPs (SOP-001 to SOP-014) covering glucose monitoring, AI session export, Nightscout, WhatsApp bot, TV dashboard, MedGemma, NHS FHIR, West Africa voice alerts\n51: - Operating manual: mental models, coding standards, workflow rules, 10 ADRs\n52: - Live docs at `https://andiekobbietks.github.io/AgentSON/`\n53: \n54: ### Examples\n55: \n56: - `examples/opencode_example.AgentSON`\n57: - `examples/minimax_example.AgentSON`\n58: - `examples/antigravity_example.AgentSON`\n59: - `examples/chrome_devtools_example.AgentSON`\n60: \n61: ### Infrastructure\n62: \n63: - PyPI package: `pip install agentson`\n64: - GitHub Actions CI: Pyrefly type checking, pytest\n65: - Branch protection: `andierules` ruleset (PR required, linear history)\n66: - CodeRabbit for AI code review (optional, not required)\n67: \n68: ### License\n69: \n70: - Changed from MIT to Apache 2.0 (patent grant + attribution)\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>",
