      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\opencode.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Opencode Session Summary — Andrea Enning (Getaway + Manufact Strategy)\n2: \n3: ## Goal\n4: - Primary: Get hired at Manufact (YC S25, MCP infrastructure startup, $6.3M seed) as MCP engineer — role is US remote or in-person only; user in NG18 UK, need to prove value via OCI/Odoo/Windows strategy\n5: - Secondary: Build Getaway travel app on the side using mcp-use SDK as portfolio piece\n6: - Long-term: Become Windows+Azure+MCP specialist; eventually move to US/remote role\n7: \n8: ## Constraints & Preferences\n9: - User is Andrea Enning (AndieKobbieTech), co-founder of Getaway travel app\n10: - Hardware: Intel i5-7300HQ, 16GB RAM, GTX 1050 (2GB), no GPU compute for ML\n11: - Location: NG18 2HY (Mansfield, Nottinghamshire) — NOT in Wales, NOT in West Midlands\n12: - User is USW graduate (BSc ICT, June 2024) — has free Startup Stiwdio access until June 2027\n13: - No LaTeX compiler installed on system — cannot compile .tex to PDF\n14: - All transcription done on CPU (no GPU); using Whisper (tiny/base) + imageio-ffmpeg bundled binary\n15: - User is NOT the original GitHub repo creator — Fizzy is; user needs repo access transferred\n16: - Fizzy left Getaway Sep 2025; user is now running it alone\n17: - Manufact (target employer) is 5-person YC S25 startup in Zurich + SF; all open roles require US remote or in-person — UK not supported yet\n18: - User has OCI Always Free tier (2 AMD + 4 ARM + 200GB storage) — cloud expertise proof via akcloud\n19: - User has Odoo Community knowledge and can join Odoo partner programme\n20: \n21: ## Progress\n22: \n23: ### Done (This Session)\n24: \n25: #### Transcription & PDF Generation\n26: - Transcribed all 4 Getaway audio files to raw PDFs, JSON with word-level timestamps, and diarised PDFs with speaker labels\n27: - Solved memory exhaustion on 79MB file by chunking into 10-minute segments\n28: - Solved Unicode encoding errors with clean() function\n29: - Generated 19-page technical documentation PDF (ADR, SFIA, user journeys, happy/error paths)\n30: - Generated corroborated ADR report and integrated ADR+Transcript PDF\n31: - Generated comprehensive essay PDF (10 chapters with 5 verbose ADRs)\n32: - Generated essay narration audio using Piper TTS (8 minutes)\n33: - Generated Jira tickets + Migration guide PDF — successfully created\n34: \n35: #### Research: Manufact (Primary Target)\n36: - **Manufact**: YC S25, $6.3M seed led by Peak XV, 5 people, Zurich + SF\n37: - **mcp-use SDK**: 7M+ downloads, 10.1k stars, 1.3k forks, 45 open issues, 49 open PRs, 336 closed\n38: - **Team**: pietrozullo (co-founder), khandrew1, tonxxd, steven — team is stretched, cannot review 49 open PRs fast enough\n39: - **Open roles**: Cloud Engineer ($100K-150K + 0.5-1.0% equity, Remote US), Open Source Engineer (same), DevRel (SF), Founding Engineer (Zurich+SF in-person), Intern (Zurich)\n40: - **Note on issues/PRs**: User was asking about Manufacturing + GitHub MCP Server for AI-driven code review/issue triage (not the repo's own bugs). Earlier issue analysis (#1220, #1718, etc.) was a separate tangent about mcp-use repo's own development backlog.\n41: - **Manufact and Microsoft are COMPLEMENTARY, not competing**: Microsoft built OS/sandbox layer (MXC, Agent 365); Manufact builds developer SDK + deployment cloud; risk from AWS/Cloudflare/Vercel/Docker (40%) exceeds risk from Microsoft (5%)\n42: \n43: #### Research: Windows MCP Ecosystem\n44: - **Windows MCP Registry**: Private developer preview (announced Build 2025)\n45: - **MXC (Microsoft Execution Containers)**: Cross-platform policy-driven execution layer for agents; early preview; NOT a deployment platform — it's a sandbox\n46: - **OpenClaw on Windows**: Alpha companion app launched Jun 2, 2026 at Build; WinUI 3, MXC sandbox, one-click .exe — Manufact has NOTHING on Windows\n47: - **Azure MCP Server**: v3.0 beta, 276 tools, twice-weekly updates\n48: - **Windows gap is Manufact's blind spot**: OpenClaw has Windows alpha; user can be their Windows strategy\n49: \n50: #### Research: Competitive Landscape (Build 2026)\n51: - **MXC (Microsoft)**: Cross-platform execution layer for agents — different layer than Manufact\n52: - **Agent 365 (Microsoft)**: Enterprise agent management — different market entirely\n53: - **Foundry MCP Server**: 38 tools for managing Foundry resources — IS an MCP server, NOT a deployment platform for YOUR servers\n54: - **WebMCP (Google)**: Browser-native client-side tools, Chrome 149 origin trial — NOT a deployment platform\n55: - **Olive (Microsoft)**: Model optimization tool — unrelated to MCP\n56: - **MAI (Microsoft)**: AI model offerings — unrelated to MCP\n57: - **Concluded**: Manufact is complementary to all of these, not competing\n58: \n59: #### Research: Odoo Payroll (Manufact's Multi-Country Pain Point)\n60: - **Community vs Enterprise**: Community has framework only; Enterprise has Swissdec 5.0 certified Swiss payroll\n61: - **Swiss payroll complexity**: 26 cantons, AHV/IV/EO 10.6%, ALV 2.2%, BVG 3.5-9%, UVG 0.1-0.8%, FAK 1.1-3.0% canton-dependent, Quellensteuer\n62: - **UK gaps**: Cannot generate FPS files for HMRC; need BrightPay/Sage integration\n63: - **Manufact value**: Deel EOR costs CHF 1,200/mo (~$14,400/yr); Odoo on OCI Always Free = $0/yr — saves Manufact ~$14K/yr\n64: \n65: #### Research: Zurich Free Tier Stack\n66: - **OCI Always Free** in eu-zurich-1: 2 AMD + 4 ARM + 200GB block + 2 ATP DBs + 10TB egress, free forever\n67: - **Azure Switzerland North**: Functions/Cosmos DB/App Service free + B1S VM 12 months\n68: - **GCP europe-west6**: Cloud Run/Functions free, no e2-micro available\n69: - **Stack**: $0/month forever — critical for Manufact's cost advantage\n70: \n71: #### Research: Odoo Partner Programme\n72: - **Learning Partner**: ~$950/yr\n73: - **Commission**: 10% Enterprise, 10% Odoo.sh; Ready: 10%+50%; Silver: 15%+50%; Gold: 20%+50%\n74: - **App Store**: 70% royalty to partner\n75: \n76: #### Research: Manufact + GitHub MCP Server for PR/Issue Workflows\n77: - **User was asking about**: Using Manufact to connect AI agents to the [GitHub MCP Server](https://github.com/github/github-mcp-server) so agents can read code, triage bugs, review PRs, and manage repo workflows\n78: - **Capabilities**: Code reviews (run diffs, leave line-specific feedback on PRs), issue triage (read reports, label, suggest fixes), automated ticket creation (TODO→GitHub issues), repo summaries in natural language\n79: - **Common challenges**: Context rot (too many tools→degraded accuracy), security risks (over-permissioned agents→prompt injection), vague error parsing (CLI errors confuse agents→hallucinated workarounds)\n80: - **Corrective note**: Earlier analysis of 45 open issues/49 open PRs on mcp-use repo was about the repo's own development backlog, NOT about the GitHub MCP Server integration feature the user was asking about\n81: \n82: #### CRITICAL: Linear Just Launched Agent-Driven Dev Workflows (June 2026)\n83: - **Announcement**: Linear launched coding sessions, automated triage, and code diffs/PRs inside Linear\n84: - **Automated Triage**: AI reconstructs bugs from reports, identifies root cause (even finds exact code line), fixes CSS/React bugs autonomously — resolves ~30% of triage issues automatically on first pass\n85: - **Agent Coding Sessions**: @Linear can be tagged in issues to start a coding session, investigate, fix, and push PRs\n86: - **Designer-to-Dev Flow**: Designers ask Linear Agent questions about codebase, get root cause analysis, delegate fixes — no repo setup needed\n87: - **PRs with Inline Fixes**: @Linear make this change in PR comments — agent edits code inline, auto-merges on approval\n88: - **Relevance to Manufact**: This is EXACTLY the \"PRs and issues\" workflow the user was asking about — Linear built what Manufact + GitHub MCP Server would enable\n89: - **Implication**: Linear is now a direct complement/threat to Manufact's value prop — agents that write code, fix PRs, and manage issues exist without Manufact\n90: \n91: #### Research: Open-Source Windows Agent Playbooks\n92: - **Claude Desktop for Windows**: MCP transport via stdio, configurable per-user/per-project\n93: - **OpenClaw WinUI 3**: GitHub repo, alpha, one-click .exe, MXC sandbox integration\n94: - **OpenClaw MCP Registry**: 47,000+ community servers, 85% production-ready, verified by DeepWiki/Agentlist\n95: - **No playbook exists** for connecting desktop agent → cloud MCP server → edge devices — this is the gap\n96: \n97: #### Research: MCP Agent Frameworks\n98: - **Anthropic SDK** (mcp, mcp-agent): Official, 100% TypeScript\n99: - **mcp-use SDK**: MIT licensed, 10.1k stars, Python + TypeScript, multi-agent, security sandbox\n100: - **mastra** (mastra-ai): TypeScript, MCP support, agent memory, workflows\n101: - **fastagent** (lastmile-ai): 8,161 stars, TypeScript/Python, MCP + A2A + AGNTCY\n102: - **Pydantic AI**: Not directly MCP-focused but usable for MCP\n103: - **No framework** currently provides a turnkey cloud-to-edge bridge for MCP\n104: \n105: #### Research: GitHub User's Profile\n106: - User account: @fizzy-fifs (Fizzy)\n107: - 47 public repos including Getaway-AI-Assistant (12 commits)\n108: - BSc Football Coaching, University of South Wales\n109: - Co-founder Getaway (Jul 2023 - Sep 2025), now Full Stack Engineer at Valent (Sep 2025 - Present)\n110: - GitHub activity through June 2026 (recently committed 6 times to Getaway-AI-Assistant Jan 2026)\n111: \n112: #### Odoo Community Payroll + HMRC RTI Status\n113: - **Community 18.0**: Has payroll framework (salary rules, payslips, contracts) + `l10n_uk` (accounting, VAT MTD) — but NO RTI/FPS submission to HMRC\n114: - **Enterprise**: Has UK payroll (PAYE, NI, student loans, auto-enrolment, RTI/FPS) — turnkey\n115: - **Third-party option**: ClickPOA UK Payroll for Community (~£200/yr) adds UK tax tables + RTI\n116: - **Recent changes**: No recent Community update closed this gap — UK payroll compliance still requires Enterprise or paid module\n117: - **Recommendation**: Demo Enterprise free for 15 days to show Manufact the full payroll flow; deploy Community on OCI Always Free for the operational demo\n118: \n119: #### Odoo Enterprise Demo Strategy\n120: - Free 15-day trial at odoo.com — one app per database\n121: - To demo multi-app integration: use Odoo.sh free trial (14 days, full stack) OR install Community on OCI with all apps (same framework minus Enterprise localizations)\n122: - Cross-database communication: not possible between separate trial accounts — use a single Odoo.sh or self-hosted instance\n123: \n124: #### Odoo Timesheets + Remote Work Tracking\n125: - **Timesheets**: Track hours per project/task, mobile app, kiosk mode, validation workflows\n126: - **HR Attendance**: Check-in/check-out, geolocation, kiosk mode\n127: - **Planning**: Shift scheduling, capacity planning\n128: - **Project**: Task-level time tracking with Gantt\n129: - **BYOD Policy**: Not natively supported as a policy workflow. Workaround: Odoo Documents (store signed BYOD agreements) + Odoo HR (employee records) + Odoo Maintenance (asset tracking) — no turnkey BYOD module exists\n130: \n131: #### LXD Cloud Dev Environment on OCI Always Free\n132: - **Architecture**: OCI ARM Ampere VM (4 OCPU, 24GB RAM) as host → LXD containers for isolated dev environments\n133: - **Setup**: `snap install lxd` on Ubuntu/Oracle Linux; LXD profiles for resource limits, network isolation\n134: - **Workflow**: Host runs code-server (VS Code in browser); each LXD container = isolated build/test environment for different projects (mcp-use, Odoo, Getaway)\n135: - **Security**: LXD namespaces = process isolation, no cross-container access, resource quotas, snapshots before risky experiments\n136: - **Cost**: $0 — OCI Always Free includes 4 ARM cores + 24GB RAM\n137: - **Benefit**: Enterprise-grade dev isolation on free infrastructure — shows Manufact you understand secure remote development workflows\n138: \n139: #### Portfolio Idea: Manufact + Linear Agent Workflow Integration\n140: - The Linear transcript shows the exact workflow Manufact should support: issue triage → agent coding session → PR with auto-fix → inline code review → merge\n141: - **Portfolio piece**: Build a Manufact-based agent that mirrors Linear's workflow but using mcp-use SDK + GitHub MCP Server\n142: - **Why it works**: Shows Manufact's own SDK can replicate what Linear just shipped — proves the platform's power\n143: - **Demo flow**: Agent reads GitHub issues → reproduces bug → generates fix → creates PR → leaves review comment — all via Manufact SDK\n144: - **No group-travel MCP server** exists — KAYAK, Priceline, Google, Reservations.ai have chatbots but no MCP for agents\n145: - **MCP Apps** launched Jan 26, 2026 — 6-18 month window before competition\n146: - **Edge deployment gap**: mcp-use SDK has no cloud hosting, no edge deployment, no MXC bridge — Manufact Cloud is just a hosting platform\n147: - **mcp-use → MXC bridge**: No concept of connecting mcp-use servers to Windows Edge devices\n148: - **mcp-use → OCI edge**: No ARM deployment optimization for MCP servers\n149: - **mcp-use → WebMCP adapter**: No browser-native MCP for Chrome agents\n150: \n151: ### In Progress\n152: - Building Windows MCP playbook to prove Manufact value\n153: - Building Getaway MCP server using mcp-use SDK as portfolio piece\n154: - Developing 4-layer pitch for Manufact application\n155: \n156: ### Blocked\n157: - Jira board at getawayai.atlassian.net requires Atlassian authentication\n158: - GitHub repo fizzy-fifs/Getaway-AI-Assistant is 404 — must get from Fizzy\n159: - getawayai.app is parked on GoDaddy — needs live site for Activate eligibility\n160: - LaTeX compiler not installed on system\n161: - Manufact roles require US remote or in-person — user in NG18 UK\n162: \n163: ## Key Decisions\n164: - **Whisper tiny model** for files > 50MB; base model for smaller files\n165: - **Context-based heuristic diarisation** (no GPU for pyannote/NeMo)\n166: - **MP3 intermediate compression** for large files\n167: - **Chunked transcription** (10-minute segments with timestamp offset)\n168: - **fpdf2 with clean() encoding filter** for Unicode→ASCII\n169: - **Two-phase approach**: transcribe to JSON first, then build PDFs from JSON\n170: - **Piper TTS** chosen for narration — CPU-only, no cloud\n171: - **Mattermost over Twake** — better Git integration, larger plugin ecosystem\n172: - **Linear over Plane** for project management — built-in Jira import\n173: - **Group-travel MCP server is uncontested** — 6-18 month window\n174: - **Andie is the founder now** — Fizzy left Sep 2025\n175: - **Manufact pitch is 4-layer**: (1) MCP server builder, (2) OCI cloud expert, (3) Odoo operational multiplier solving multi-country payroll, (4) Windows + Azure + OCI champion bridging Manufact Cloud to MXC\n176: - **Fix mcp-use #1220 as entry point** — Windows double-close bug demonstrates expertise, gets name in contributors\n177: - **Manufact and Microsoft are complementary**: Microsoft = OS/infrastructure layer; Manufact = developer SDK layer\n178: \n179: ## Next Steps\n180: \n181: ### Immediate (This Week)\n182: 1. ~~Fix mcp-use #1220~~ — tangential suggestion; user's focus is on Manufacturing + GitHub MCP Server integration for AI-driven PR/issue workflows, not the repo's own bugs\n183: 2. **Build Getaway MCP server** using mcp-use SDK — portfolio piece showing MCP building + SDK experience\n184: 3. **Build Linear-workflow clone** using mcp-use SDK + GitHub MCP Server — replicates Linear's new agent-driven PR/triage flow as Manufact portfolio piece\n185: 3. **Message Fizzy** — request GitHub repo access transfer\n186: 4. **Install LaTeX compiler** (MiKTeX or use Overleaf) — compile master CV\n187: \n188: ### Short-Term (2-4 Weeks)\n189: 5. **Apply to Manufact** — Cloud Engineer or Open Source Engineer with 4-layer pitch (MCP + OCI + Odoo + Windows)\n190: 6. **Set up Odoo Community on OCI Always Free** — proof of concept for Manufact's payroll solution\n191: 7. **Build Windows MCP Registry concept** — example package for mcp-use integration\n192: 8. **Draft Loom script** — 2-3 minute video for Manufact application\n193: \n194: ### Medium-Term (1-3 Months)\n195: 9. **Apply to Alacrity Foundation** — £18K stipend + £250K investment\n196: 10. **NatWest Accelerator** — sign up for Sheffield hub\n197: 11. **Email Zein Zaher** (Tramshed Tech) — ask about Sovereign AI Fund intro\n198: 12. **Connect with Will Bushby on LinkedIn** — Welsh launch, Getaway AI\n199: 13. **Register for NatWest Pitch Cardiff** (Sep 10, 2026)\n200: 14. **Apply to NVIDIA Inception** — free, unlocks $150K+ elsewhere\n201: 15. **Get getawayai.app live** — landing page on Lovable.dev for Activate eligibility\n202: 16. **Set up SeedLegals** — formalise founder status\n203: \n204: ## Critical Context\n205: - **Manufact**: 5-person YC S25 startup, $6.3M seed, mcp-use SDK (7M downloads, 10.1k stars), HQ SF + Zurich\n206: - **User's value**: Only candidate bringing OCI + Odoo + Windows + MCP together — no other applicant has this combination\n207: - **Timing**: 6-week window (Parkinson's Law) to build portfolio; 3-6 month window before competition captures Windows MCP\n208: - **Risk profile**: Linear (new agent workflows) 20% — directly ships what Manufact enables; Microsoft 5%; AWS/Cloudflare/Vercel/Docker 40%; Manufact runway 30%; Foundry Toolboxes 15%; MCP replacement 10%\n209: - **mcp-use contributor landscape**: 49 open PRs, team stretched; contributions valued and visible\n210: - **OpenClaw already on Windows**: Alpha launched Jun 2, 2026 at Build — Manufact has nothing; user can fill this gap\n211: - **Getaway repo**: getaway-ai org has 5 private repos; user @andiekobbietks listed as member; Fizzy last committed Jan 27, 2026\n212: - **User health**: blood malformation (Type C variant), anemia, vitamin D deficiency\n213: - **Joseph**: broke Mac screen ~Sep 2025, limited development capacity\n214: \n215: ## Relevant Files\n216: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\` — all output directory\n217: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\Getaway_Technical_Documentation_ADR_SFIA.pdf` — 19-page technical doc\n218: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\Getaway_Integrated_ADR_Transcript.pdf` — integrated ADR+transcript\n219: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\Getaway_Complete_Essay_ADR.pdf` — 10-chapter essay\n220: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\Getaway_Essay_Narration.wav` — 8-minute TTS narration\n221: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Getaway_Transcriptions\\Getaway_Jira_Migration_Guide.pdf` — Jira reconstruction\n222: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Andrea_Enning_Master_CV.tex` — Master CV (ModernCV green format)\n223: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\_chat 9.txt` — Getaway Co-founders WhatsApp\n224: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\_chat 4 (1).txt` — Santander UK Universities post\n225: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\opencode_session_export.json` — first chat export (23.9KB)\n226: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\opencode_full_session_export.json` — comprehensive chat export (48.2KB)\n227: - `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\opencode\\` — opencode temp directory (150+ files, no chat history)\n\n(End of file - total 227 lines)\n</content>",
