      "text": "Here's an honest assessment of your repo:\n\n**What's good:**\n- Clean README with architecture diagram, tool landscape, schema docs\n- 14 SOPs present and documented\n- 11 ADRs (001-011) — solid decision trail\n- 6 readers implemented (opencode, minimax, antigravity, libre, chrome_devtools, claude_code)\n- v0.1.1 release tagged\n- Apache 2.0 license correctly stated\n\n**Issues I found:**\n\n1. **Reader count mismatch** — README claims \"Working (7)\" in the pie chart, but only 6 reader files exist in `/readers/`. Which 7th reader is being counted?\n\n2. **Unpushed work:**\n   - `adr-011-rename-agenson-to-agentsone.md` — untracked, not on GitHub\n   - Modified `CHANGELOG.md`, `README.md`, `SOP-004` — not committed\n   - `agentson_cli.py`, `install.ps1` — untracked\n\n3. **FreeStyle Libre connection unclear** — The `libre.py` reader exists, SOPs 001-003 cover it, but the README doesn't prominently connect this to your personal health journey (Type C blood malformation, anemia). This is actually your most unique use case — the reason the project exists.\n\n4. **The `.ailog` history is buried** — The origin story (Chrome DevTools → `.ailog` → AgentSON) isn't in the README. ADR-004 mentions it but it's not on the main page.\n\n**What would make it reflect your journey better:**\n- Add a \"Why this exists\" section tying the FreeStyle Libre reader to your health data liberation story\n- Push ADR-011 and the modified files\n- Fix the reader count (6 or 7?)\n\nWant me to fix any of these?",
