      "text": "The user wants to understand if their GitHub repo reflects their development journey well. Let me compare what's on GitHub vs what's local.\n\nFrom the GitHub page:\n- 26 commits\n- v0.1.1 release\n- Folders: SOPs, cli, docs, exporters, importers, pwa, readers, spec, supabase, tests, training, viewers/web\n- Files: .gitignore, CHANGELOG.md, LICENSE, MANIFEST.in, PERSONAS-AND-USER-STORIES.md, PRD.md, README.md, ROADMAP.md, index.html, pyproject.toml, setup.pyFrom local git status:\n- Modified: CHANGELOG.md, README.md, SOPs/SOP-004-Exporting-AI-Sessions.md\n- Untracked: agentson_cli.py, check_opencode.py, check_status.ps1, docs/standards/adrs/adr-011-rename-agenson-to-agentsone.md, install.ps1\n\nFrom local readers directory:\n- __init__.py\n- antigravity.py\n- chrome_devtools.py\n- claude_code.py\n- libre.py\n- minimax.py\n- opencode.py\n\nThat's 6 readers, but the README claims 7 working readers. Let me check what's actually there vs what's claimed.\n\nThe README says:\n- \"Working (7)\" in the pie chart\n- But only lists 6 readers in the repo structure\n\nAlso, the SOPs directory shows 14 SOPs, which matches the README claim.\n\nThe ADRs directory shows 11 ADRs (001-011), which is good.\n\nKey issues I see:\n1. Reader count mismatch - README says 7 working, but I only see 6 reader files\n2. ADR-011 is untracked (not pushed to GitHub)\n3. Some modified files not committed (CHANGELOG.md, README.md, SOP-004)\n4. Several untracked files not pushed\n\nLet me give the user an honest assessment.",
