      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\ROADMAP.md\", \"limit\": 100}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\ROADMAP.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentSON Roadmap\n2: \n3: **Last updated:** 05 July 2026\n4: \n5: ## Vision\n6: \n7: AgentSON is the universal interchange format for AI agent session traces. This roadmap prioritizes readers by RICE score (Reach × Impact × Confidence / Effort) to maximize coverage of the 33-tool AI coding landscape.\n8: \n9: ## RICE Scoring\n10: \n11: | Factor | Definition | Scale |\n12: |--------|-----------|-------|\n13: | **Reach** | Monthly active users who would benefit | Thousands |\n14: | **Impact** | Value the reader adds (portability, training data) | 1 (low) – 3 (high) |\n15: | **Confidence** | How sure we are about estimates | 0.5 – 1.0 |\n16: | **Effort** | Person-months to build and test | 0.5 – 4.0 |\n17: \n18: **RICE = (Reach × Impact × Confidence) / Effort**\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Tier 1: Core Market (Priority: Highest)\n23: \n24: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n25: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n26: | 1 | **Cursor** | Anysphere/SpaceX | 2000 | 3 | 0.9 | 2.0 | **2700** | 🔜 Planned |\n27: | 2 | **Claude Code** | Anthropic | 1500 | 3 | 0.8 | 0.0 | **∞** | ✅ Working |\n28: | 3 | **Kiro** | AWS/Amazon | 800 | 3 | 0.7 | 1.5 | **1120** | 🔜 Planned |\n29: | 4 | **Codex CLI** | OpenAI | 1200 | 3 | 0.8 | 1.5 | **1920** | 🔜 Planned |\n30: | 5 | **Gemini CLI** | Google | 1000 | 2 | 0.7 | 1.0 | **1400** | 🔜 Planned |\n31: | 6 | **Windsurf/Devin Desktop** | Cognition | 600 | 2 | 0.6 | 1.5 | **480** | 🔜 Planned |\n32: \n33: **Rationale:** These tools have the largest user bases and generate the richest session traces. Cursor and Claude Code alone represent ~3.5B monthly sessions. Building readers here gives AgentSON access to 80%+ of the AI coding market.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Tier 2: Open Source (Priority: High)\n38: \n39: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n40: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n41: | 7 | **opencode** | Anomaly | 6500 | 3 | 1.0 | 0.0 | **∞** | ✅ Working |\n42: | 8 | **Cline** | Cline Labs | 500 | 3 | 0.9 | 1.0 | **1350** | 🔜 Planned |\n43: | 9 | **Aider** | Paul Gauthier | 400 | 3 | 0.9 | 0.8 | **1350** | 🔜 Planned |\n44: | 10 | **Goose** | Block | 200 | 2 | 0.7 | 1.0 | **280** | 🔜 Planned |\n45: | 11 | **OpenHands** | All-Hands | 150 | 2 | 0.7 | 1.0 | **210** | 🔜 Planned |\n46: | 12 | **Zed** | Zed Industries | 300 | 2 | 0.6 | 1.5 | **240** | 🔜 Planned |\n47: \n48: **Rationale:** Open-source tools have BYOK users who care about data ownership. These users are AgentSON's natural advocates. opencode already works. Cline and Aider are next because their users actively choose data sovereignty.\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Tier 3: Extensions (Priority: Medium)\n53: \n54: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n55: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n56: | 13 | **GitHub Copilot** | Microsoft | 5000 | 2 | 0.8 | 2.0 | **4000** | 🔜 Planned |\n57: | 14 | **Amazon Q** | AWS | 400 | 2 | 0.7 | 1.5 | **373** | 🔜 Planned |\n58: | 15 | **JetBrains AI** | JetBrains | 300 | 2 | 0.7 | 1.5 | **280** | 🔜 Planned |\n59: | 16 | **Sourcegraph Cody** | Sourcegraph | 100 | 1 | 0.6 | 1.0 | **60** | 🔜 Planned |\n60: | 17 | **Qodo** | Qodo | 50 | 1 | 0.5 | 1.0 | **25** | 🔜 Planned |\n61: | 18 | **Augment Code** | Augment | 80 | 1 | 0.5 | 1.0 | **40** | 🔜 Planned |\n62: | 19 | **Continue** | Continue | 200 | 2 | 0.8 | 1.0 | **320** | 🔜 Planned |\n63: | 20 | **Tabnine** | Tabnine | 150 | 1 | 0.7 | 1.0 | **105** | 🔜 Planned |\n64: \n65: **Rationale:** Extensions wrap existing IDEs. High reach (Copilot alone has 5M+ users) but lower impact because they inherit the host IDE's storage. Copilot is highest priority here due to sheer market share.\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## Tier 4: Builders (Priority: Low-Medium)\n70: \n71: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n72: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n73: | 21 | **Bolt.new** | StackBlitz | 200 | 1 | 0.5 | 1.5 | **67** | 🔜 Planned |\n74: | 22 | **v0** | Vercel | 300 | 1 | 0.5 | 1.5 | **100** | 🔜 Planned |\n75: | 23 | **Lovable** | Lovable | 150 | 1 | 0.5 | 1.5 | **50** | 🔜 Planned |\n76: | 24 | **Replit** | Replit | 500 | 1 | 0.6 | 2.0 | **150** | 🔜 Planned |\n77: \n78: **Rationale:** Builder traces are prompt→app, not agent→code. Lower training value but still portable. Replit has the largest user base.\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Tier 5: Orchestrators (Priority: Low)\n83: \n84: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n85: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n86: | 25 | **amux** | amux | 50 | 2 | 0.5 | 1.5 | **33** | 🔜 Planned |\n87: | 26 | **Claude Squad** | Claude Squad | 30 | 2 | 0.5 | 1.0 | **30** | 🔜 Planned |\n88: | 27 | **Kilo Code** | Kilo Code | 80 | 2 | 0.6 | 1.0 | **96** | 🔜 Planned |\n89: | 28 | **dmux** | dmux | 20 | 2 | 0.5 | 1.0 | **20** | 🔜 Planned |\n90: \n91: **Rationale:** Orchestrators manage fleets of agents. Traces are aggregate, not individual. Lower training value but useful for fleet analytics.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Tier 6: Autonomous (Priority: Low)\n96: \n97: | # | Tool | Company | Reach | Impact | Confidence | Effort | RICE | Status |\n98: |---|------|---------|-------|--------|------------|--------|------|--------|\n99: | 29 | **Devin** | Cognition | 100 | 2 | 0.6 | 2.0 | **60** | 🔜 Planned |\n100: | 30 | **Blitzy** | Blitzy | 20 | 1 | 0.4 | 2.0 | **4** | 🔜 Planned |\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 175. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>",
