      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\standards\\workflow.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Workflow Rules\n2: \n3: How I manage work day-to-day.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Git Workflow\n8: \n9: ### Branch Naming\n10: \n11: ```\n12: feat/<short-description>     — new feature\n13: fix/<short-description>      — bug fix\n14: docs/<short-description>     — documentation only\n15: refactor/<short-description> — code cleanup\n16: ```\n17: \n18: Examples:\n19: - `feat/chrome-devtools-reader`\n20: - `fix/libre-csv-encoding`\n21: - `docs/sop-renderer`\n22: \n23: ### Commit Messages\n24: \n25: Format: `type(scope): description`\n26: \n27: Keep under 72 characters for the first line. Add body if needed.\n28: \n29: ### Main Branch\n30: \n31: `master` is the production branch. All changes go through PRs. No direct pushes.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## PR Process\n36: \n37: ### What Goes in a PR\n38: \n39: - One logical change per PR\n40: - Tests if adding new functionality\n41: - Updated documentation if changing behavior\n42: - No unrelated changes mixed in\n43: \n44: ### PR Title\n45: \n46: Same format as commit messages: `type(scope): description`\n47: \n48: ### What Gets Reviewed\n49: \n50: For a solo project, self-review is fine. But read the diff before merging. Check:\n51: - No PII leaked\n52: - No secrets committed\n53: - Tests pass\n54: - Documentation updated\n55: \n56: ### Merging\n57: \n58: Use squash merge for clean history. The branch name becomes the commit message context.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## Deployment\n63: \n64: ### GitHub Pages\n65: \n66: - Source: `master` branch, `/docs` folder\n67: - Deploy: automatic on push to master\n68: - `.nojekyll` required (Google Fonts URLs have `?` characters)\n69: \n70: ### Python Package\n71: \n72: - Build: `python -m build`\n73: - Publish: PyPI trusted publishing (OIDC, no stored tokens)\n74: - Version: follow semver in `pyproject.toml`\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Incident Response\n79: \n80: ### Something Breaks\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 114. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>",
