      "type": "answer",
      "text": "## Goal\n- Improve the AgentSON Wiki Deployment Cheat Sheet PDF (fix overlapping text, add breathing room, golden ratio spacing) and expand it with an SOP for creating wikis programmatically using OpenCode and its free tiers\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- PDF must have no overlapping text — clean typography with golden ratio (PHI = 1.618) spacing\n- User wants the SOP to cover: how to create a wiki, how to do it programmatically, and especially how to do it using OpenCode and its free tiers\n- No PII in repo, no telemetry, vendor neutral, single file output, honest labels\n- Classic PAT with `repo` scope for wiki pushes; fine-grained tokens cannot push to wiki\n- License is Apache 2.0 (user deliberately chose this)\n- ReportLab used for PDF generation (installed via `pip install reportlab`)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- ✅ ADR PR #14 merged\n- ✅ v0.1.0 tag + release already published on GitHub\n- ✅ README \"Why This Exists\" section added (ties FreeStyle Libre 2 to health data liberation)\n- ✅ README reader count fixed (6 working, not 7)\n- ✅ Duplicate GDPR content removed from \"Why AgentSON Matters\"\n- ✅ README changes committed locally (`d4ea59e`)\n- ✅ 9 wiki pages created in `agentsong/wiki/` (Home, Getting-Started, Schema, Readers, ADRs, SOPs, Coding-Standards, Mental-Models, Contributing)\n- ✅ Wiki cloned, files copied, committed, and pushed to GitHub wiki via classic PAT\n- ✅ OpenCode database queried — found FreeStyle session ID (`ses_1069f6208ffeXozEyNyMW6RXOO`, slug: gentle-engine)\n- ✅ License confirmed: Apache 2.0 was deliberate user choice (patent grants + attribution)\n- ✅ `.ailog` history clarified — predecessor to AgentSON, rebranded with amber tokens\n- ✅ AgentSON_Wiki_Cheatsheet.pdf generated (v3 with golden ratio spacing)\n- ✅ ReportLab installed (`pip install reportlab`)\n\n### In Progress\n- PDF still has overlapping/poor spacing — user says \"STILL LOOK IS LIKE IS NOT BREATHING\"\n- Need to add SOP for creating wikis programmatically using OpenCode free tiers\n\n### Blocked\n- README push to remote blocked (fine-grained token can't authenticate; needs classic PAT push)\n- ADR-011 + modified files unpushed (same blocker)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- Apache 2.0 license chosen deliberately by user for patent grants\n- AgentSON is the one project name; `.ailog`/`ailog` repo treated as scrap material per ADR-011\n- Classic PAT (not fine-grained) required for wiki pushes — embedded in URL format\n- Golden ratio (PHI = 1.618) applied to line spacing, leading, and padding in PDF\n- Health data liberation story (FreeStyle Libre 2) is the core \"Why This Exists\" narrative\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Fix PDF spacing — make it \"breathe\" (larger margins, more whitespace between sections, possibly landscape or multi-column)\n2. Write SOP for creating wikis programmatically using OpenCode free tiers (MiMo V2.5 Free, Claude Sonnet 4.6, etc.)\n3. Add that SOP content to the cheatsheet PDF\n4. Push README + ADR-011 to remote using classic PAT\n5. Re-generate and verify final PDF has no overlaps\n\n## Critical Context\n- User has Type C blood malformation, anemia — FreeStyle Libre 2 is critical health monitoring for their mother\n- User wants to potentially file ICO complaint against Abbott for GDPR Article 20 data portability violation\n- OpenCode sessions: FreeStyle Libre session `ses_1069f6208ffeXozEyNyMW6RXOO` (gentle-engine), current session `ses_0cbd91919ffeyYUXTVAIBZXQu7` (jolly-cabin)\n- OpenCode DB at `~/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db` (1.7GB)\n- PDF font sizes reduced to 7.5-8.5pt, margins at 50pt, but user still finds it cramped\n- The `.ailog` repo on GitHub (`andiekobbietks/ailog`) was built by MiniMax-M3 — has fabricated benchmark numbers, should not be promoted\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md`: Modified with \"Why This Exists\" section, reader count fix, GDPR cleanup — committed but not pushed\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\wiki_cheatsheet.py`: PDF generation script (v3) — needs further spacing fixes and SOP expansion\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\wiki\\AgentSON_Wiki_Cheatsheet.pdf`: Generated cheatsheet PDF — user says still overlapping, needs breathing room\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\wiki\\*.md`: 9 wiki pages (Home, Getting-Started, Schema, Readers, ADRs, SOPs, Coding-Standards, Mental-Models, Contributing)\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AgentSON.wiki\\`: Cloned wiki repo with pushed pages\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\standards\\adrs\\adr-011-rename-agenson-to-agentsone.md`: Untracked, not pushed\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.local\\share\\opencode\\opencode.db`: OpenCode session database\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\CHANGELOG.md`: Modified, not pushed\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\readers\\libre.py`: FreeStyle Libre 2 CSV reader — first reader built\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\PRD.md`: Product requirements document\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\ROADMAP.md`: RICE-scored roadmap (33 tools, 7 tiers)",
