      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AgentSON.wiki\\SOPs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)\n2: \n3: 14 SOPs covering health data, AI sessions, and infrastructure.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## SOP Index\n8: \n9: | # | Title | Category |\n10: |---|-------|----------|\n11: | 001 | [Reading FreeStyle Libre 2 Sensor](SOP-001) | Health |\n12: | 002 | [Converting Libre Data to AgentSON](SOP-002) | Health |\n13: | 003 | [Viewing Glucose Data in Browser](SOP-003) | Health |\n14: | 004 | [Exporting AI Sessions](SOP-004) | AI Sessions |\n15: | 005 | [Searching AI Sessions](SOP-005) | AI Sessions |\n16: | 006 | [Sharing Data with Doctors](SOP-006) | Health |\n17: | 007 | [Setting Up Nightscout Server](SOP-007) | Infrastructure |\n18: | 008 | [WhatsApp Bot Setup](SOP-008) | Infrastructure |\n19: | 009 | [TV Dashboard Setup](SOP-009) | Infrastructure |\n20: | 010 | [Setting Up MedGemma HAI-DEF](SOP-010) | Health/AI |\n21: | 011 | [Fine-tuning MedGemma on Glucose Data](SOP-011) | Health/AI |\n22: | 012 | [Setting Up Juggluco on Mother's Phone](SOP-012) | Health |\n23: | 013 | [NHS FHIR Integration](SOP-013) | Health |\n24: | 014 | [West Africa Voice Alerts](SOP-014) | Health/Localization |\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Health SOPs\n29: \n30: ### SOP-001: Reading FreeStyle Libre 2 Sensor\n31: \n32: Read glucose data from FreeStyle Libre 2 continuous glucose monitor using NFC.\n33: \n34: **Prerequisites:**\n35: - FreeStyle Libre 2 sensor\n36: - Android phone with NFC\n37: - LibreLink app installed\n38: \n39: **Steps:**\n40: 1. Open LibreLink app\n41: 2. Scan sensor with NFC\n42: 3. Export CSV from app\n43: 4. Run `agentson import --tool libre --input libre_data.csv`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### SOP-002: Converting Libre Data to AgentSON\n48: \n49: Convert FreeStyle Libre 2 CSV export to AgentSON format.\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: # Import Libre CSV\n53: agentson import --tool libre --input libre_data.csv --output session.AgentSON\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ### SOP-003: Viewing Glucose Data in Browser\n59: \n60: View glucose data in the web viewer with trend charts.\n61: \n62: 1. Open `docs/viewer/index.html`\n63: 2. Drag and drop `.AgentSON` file\n64: 3. View trend chart and statistics\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## AI Session SOPs\n69: \n70: ### SOP-004: Exporting AI Sessions\n71: \n72: Export sessions from any supported tool.\n73: \n74: ```bash\n75: # Export from opencode\n76: agentson export --tool opencode --session ses_xxx --output ./sessions/\n77: \n78: # Export from Claude Code\n79: agentson export --tool claude-code --session session_xxx --output ./sessions/\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### SOP-005: Searching AI Sessions\n85: \n86: Full-text search across all exported sessions.\n87: \n88: ```bash\n89: # Search for a keyword\n90: agentson search \"nightscout\" --tool opencode\n91: \n92: # Search across all tools\n93: agentson search \"auth bug\"\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ## Infrastructure SOPs\n99: \n100: ### SOP-007: Setting Up Nightscout Server\n101: \n102: Self-host Nightscout for glucose data cloud sync.\n103: \n104: **Prerequisites:**\n105: - Oracle Cloud Always Free tier (or any VPS)\n106: - Docker installed\n107: \n108: **Steps:**\n109: 1. Deploy Nightscout Docker container\n110: 2. Configure MongoDB\n111: 3. Set API secret\n112: 4. Connect LibreLink app\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### SOP-013: NHS FHIR Integration\n117: \n118: Share glucose data with NHS doctors via FHIR API.\n119: \n120: **Status:** Planned — requires NHS Digital FHIR credentials\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## Health/AI SOPs\n125: \n126: ### SOP-010: Setting Up MedGemma HAI-DEF\n127: \n128: Set up Google's MedGemma model for glucose data analysis.\n129: \n130: ### SOP-011: Fine-tuning MedGemma on Glucose Data\n131: \n132: Fine-tune MedGemma on personal glucose data for personalized insights.\n\n(End of file - total 132 lines)\n</content>",
